    "name": "pressure_fed_lox_kerosene_system_c18b6692",
    "description": "Design a pressure-fed rocket engine feed system using LOX (liquid oxygen) and kerosene as propellants, with nitrogen (GN2) as the pressurant gas. The system consists of three tanks (GN2, LOX, kerosene), pressurization lines from GN2 to each propellant tank, and feed lines from each propellant tank to the engine. The GN2 tank provides pressurization to maintain propellant tank pressures, forcing propellants through the feed lines to the engine. FIXED quantities: component architecture (GN2 tank, LOX tank, kerosene tank, engine, pressurization lines, feed lines). TUNABLE quantities: tank initial pressures, volumes, temperatures; line diameters and lengths; engine flow characteristics. The design must achieve stable propellant flow to the engine with physically realistic pressures and temperatures throughout.",
